Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Pick and chop @thyme{1/2%tsp} leaves from sprigs. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating greens and whites. Zest 1 tsp zest from @lemon{1}, then quarter. Place @tricolor peppercorns{1%tbsp} in a #zip-close bag{}; crush with a #rolling pin{} or a heavy pan.

Toss @carrots{16%oz} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast until tender, about ~{15%minutes}, tossing halfway. Meanwhile, halve @fingerling potatoes{24%oz} lengthwise. Place in a large, #microwave-safe bowl{} and cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave on high for ~{7%minutes}; keep in microwave until step 6.

== Cheese Sauce ==

Melt @garlic herb butter{2%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Whisk in @flour{1%tbsp} and let cook ~{30%seconds}. Pour in @milk{13.5%oz} and whisk until smooth. Add a few whole thyme sprigs (use the rest as you like), scallion whites, and @salt{pinch} to pot. Bring to a simmer and let bubble until thickened, about ~{2%minutes}.

Remove pot with sauce from heat, then stir in @Gruyère cheese{1/2%cup} and half the @Parmesan cheese{1/2%cup}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover and set aside.

== Steak ==

Pat @sirloin steak{24%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with plenty of @salt{} and crushed peppercorns (save some pepper for later). Heat a drizzle @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Set aside on a #cutting board{}. Reduce heat under pan to medium.

== Carrots ==

Once carrots are done, toss with lemon zest and a few squeezes of lemon juice. Preheat broiler to high.

== Gravy ==

Add @water{1/2%cup} and @beef demi-glace{1} to pan used for steak over medium heat. Cook until just thickened, about ~{2%minutes}. Remove from heat, stir in @butter{2%tbsp}(plain), and season with @salt{} and crushed peppercorns.

== Potato Gratin Crust ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, remaining Parmesan, chopped thyme, a large drizzle @olive oil{}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Drain any water from potatoes, then place in a #baking dish{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then pour cheese sauce over top. Sprinkle crust over. Broil until golden brown, about ~{3%minutes}.

Divide steak between #plates{} (slice first if desired). Drizzle with gravy. Serve with carrots and potatoes on the side. Garnish everything with scallion greens.